  "prompt": "What are the strongest majors in terms of job prospects and what are the weakest majors at Mercer University?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, I don't have specific information about the job prospects for individual majors at Mercer University. Generally speaking, job prospects for different majors can vary greatly based on current market trends, industry demands, and economic conditions.\n\nTypically, majors in fields such as engineering, computer science, healthcare, business, and data science tend to offer strong job prospects across many universities due to high demand and competitive salaries. On the other hand, majors like arts, humanities, and some social sciences sometimes have fewer direct job opportunities and may require additional education or experience to achieve comparable job prospects.\n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding job prospects for specific majors at Mercer University, I would recommend consulting:\n\n1. Mercer University's career services or academic advising center, which often have resources and statistics on job placement and industry trends for their graduates.\n2. Alumni networks and professional associations related to your field of interest.\n3. Data from sources such as the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics, which provide information on job outlook for various professions.\n\nBy combining these resources, you can get a more comprehensive understanding of which majors are currently strong and which might have weaker prospects in the context of Mercer University.",
